_2.png 2x"><source media="(min-width: 360px)" data-srcset="https://img2.storyblok.com/448x0/filters:format(png):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 1x, https://img2.storyblok.com/896x0/filters:format(png):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 2x" srcset="https://img2.storyblok.com/448x0/filters:format(png):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png, https://img2.storyblok.com/896x0/filters:format(png):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 2x"> <source type="image/webp" data-srcset="https://img2.storyblok.com/328x0/filters:format(webp):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 1x, https://img2.storyblok.com/656x0/filters:format(webp):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 2x" srcset="https://img2.storyblok.com/328x0/filters:format(webp):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png, https://img2.storyblok.com/656x0/filters:format(webp):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 2x"> <source data-srcset="https://img2.storyblok.com/328x0/filters:format(png):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 1x, https://img2.storyblok.com/656x0/filters:format(png):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 2x" srcset="https://img2.storyblok.com/328x0/filters:format(png):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png, https://img2.storyblok.com/656x0/filters:format(png):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png 2x"> <img alt="Job Descriptions in vacancy ads" data-src="https://img2.storyblok.com/328x0/filters:format(png):quality(75)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png" src="https://img2.storyblok.com/328x0/filters:format(png):blur(30):quality(30)/f/145847/1074x400/0cc39db582/jd_2.png" class="lazy undefined"></picture> <!----> <!----></div></div><div data-v-3cb16c5a><!----> <div data-v-3cb16c5a><article class="blog-markdown mx-auto max-w-screen-md prose prose-hr:h-[8px] prose-hr:m-0 prose-hr:border-none prose-headings:my-0 prose-headings:font-700 prose-headings:text-charcoal prose-h1:mb-[32px] prose-h1:mt-[48px] prose-h1:text-[34px] prose-h1:leading-[40px] prose-h1:tracking-[0.25px] md:prose-h1:text-[48px] md:prose-h1:leading-[56px] md:prose-h1:tracking-[0px] lg:prose-h1:text-[60px] lg:prose-h1:leading-[72px] prose-h2:text-[24px] prose-h2:leading-[32px] prose-h2:tracking-[0px] prose-h2:mt-[48px] prose-h2:mb-[24px] md:prose-h2:text-[34px] md:prose-h2:leading-[40px] md:prose-h2:tracking-[0.25px] lg:prose-h2:text-[40px] lg:prose-h2:leading-[48px] lg:prose-h2:tracking-[0px] prose-h3:text-[20px] prose-h3:leading-[32px] prose-h3:tracking-[0.15px] prose-h3:mb-[20px] md:prose-h3:text-[24px] md:prose-h3:leading-[32px] md:prose-h3:tracking-[0px] prose-p:m-0 prose-p:font-500 prose-p:text-charcoal prose-p:text-[14px] prose-p:leading-[24px] prose-p:tracking-[0.1px] prose-p:mb-[20px] md:prose-p:text-[16px] md:prose-p:leading-[32px] md:prose-p:tracking-[0.15px] prose-a:text-blue prose-strong:font-700 prose-blockquote:border-none prose-blockquote:relative prose-p:before:content-[] prose-blockquote:not-italic prose-blockquote:m-0 prose-blockquote:p-[8px_0px_8px_16px] md:prose-blockquote:p-[8px_0px_8px_26px] prose-blockquote:before:absolute prose-blockquote:before:inset-0 prose-blockquote:before:w-[4px] prose-blockquote:before:bg-blue prose-blockquote:before:rounded-full prose-blockquote:before:left-0 md:prose-blockquote:before:w-[6px] prose-ol:pl-[16px] prose-ol:mb-[20px] prose-ol:list-decimal md:prose-ol:pl-[26px] prose-li:marker:proportional-nums prose-ul:pl-[16px] prose-ul:mb-[20px] prose-ul:list-disc md:prose-ul:pl-[26px] prose-li:font-500 prose-li:text-charcoal prose-li:text-[16px] prose-li:leading-[32px] prose-li:m-0 prose-li:p-0 prose-table:table-fixed prose-table:border-[0px] prose-table:text-charcoal prose-table:text-[14px] prose-table:leading-[24px] md:prose-table:text-[16px] prose-tr:grid prose-tr:divide-y-[3px] prose-tr:divide-lavender prose-tr:border-[0px] sm:prose-tr:border-[3px] sm:prose-tr:border-lavender sm:prose-tr:table-row prose-td:p-[32px] sm:prose-td:border-[3px] sm:prose-td:border-lavender prose-th:p-[32px] empty:prose-th:hidden sm:empty:prose-th:table-cell sm:prose-th:border-[3px] sm:prose-th:border-lavender prose-thead:border-[3px] prose-thead:border-lavender prose-tbody:border-[3px] prose-tbody:border-lavender prose-tbody:divide-y-[3px] prose-tbody:divide-lavender"><h2 id="otherimportantaspectswhenwritingajobad">Other Important Aspects When Writing A Job Ad</h2>
<h2 id="completeness">Completeness</h2>
<p>A good job description needs to provide all the information necessary for potential candidates to decide about applying. This means listing everything that's required of them, as well as what they'll need in order to succeed.&#xA0; It should include any pre-requisites or requirements such as experience, education, age, competencies etc. If your company is hiring managers, it might be useful to mention how many years of management experience are needed. Hence, applicants know if their background matches up with what you're looking for! Make sure you have a detailed list of tasks and responsibilities assigned for this role, so people understand exactly what will be expected from them on day one!</p>
<h2 id="salary">Salary</h2>
<p>Candidates need to know if the salary you're offering fits their expectations upfront. So make sure this is included on the job posting! For example, if your company doesn't have a standard pay scale, it might be helpful to include an estimated range so people can decide if they'll be able to afford to live in your area. The hiring manager should also mention what benefits are offered and vacation time or other perks that will help employees feel valued. This information should all be included at the beginning of the job description rather than buried later in the text because many people won't want to apply until they understand exactly how much money they could earn working there.</p>
<h2 id="professionalperspectives">Professional Perspectives</h2>
<p>A job description is a perfect opportunity to showcase your company's best features and attract top talent! If you can't find any positive aspects of working for your business, it might be time to reevaluate. Remember: candidates are always looking for reasons not to apply, so make sure they have plenty of great things about this role at your company that will motivate them. This could include opportunities for growth or professional development, working conditions or atmosphere, even something as simple as making a difference in people's lives! The more attractive benefits you advertise here, the better chance you'll have at getting someone truly interested in joining forces with your team.</p>
<h2 id="discriminatorywording">Discriminatory Wording</h2>
<p>Since job descriptions are used in recruitment by human resources, it's important to avoid any discriminatory language for job seekers. Always keep in mind that these ads could be seen by people of all genders and backgrounds! If you've written &quot;ideal candidate&quot; or something similar, try rewording your description so only the necessary skill set is required. For example, Hiring managers shouldn't require applicants to have a certain level of education unless this truly matters for the role they're applying to. So instead of writing out their exact degree title (i.e., bachelor's or master's), mention what type of higher learning would be beneficial if they don't have one already (examples include college diploma/certificate). The same applies when listing previous work experience - hiring managers shouldn't list specific years, simply mention how many years of experience they'll need to use.</p>
<p>In conclusion, job descriptions are essential for many reasons and should be completed as thoroughly as possible. The more information hiring managers include the better chance they'll attract quality candidates who genuinely want to work there!</p>
